                <head>“Lady Lady”</head>
                
                <lg><l>Lady, Lady, I saw your face,</l>
                <l>Dark as night withholding a star . . .</l>
                <l>The chisel fell, or it might have been</l>
                <l>You had borne so long the yoke of men.</l></lg>
                
                <lg><l>Lady, Lady, I saw your hands,</l>
                <l>Twisted, awry- like crumpled roots,</l>
                <l>Bleached poor white in a sudsy tub,</l>
                <l>Wrinkled and drawn from your rub-a-dub.</l></lg>
                
                <lg><l>Lady, Lady, I saw your heart,</l>
                <l>And altared there in its darksome place</l>
                <l>Were the tongues of flame the ancients knew,</l>
                <l>Where the good God sits to spangle through.</l></lg>
                
                <byline>Anne Spencer</byline>
            </div>
